column6: This appears to be leaning towards scale free, we have a linear downtrend that turns into a heavy tail.

When compared to 2 random networks: lower avg degree, much smaller diameter, similar modularity, higher clustering coef, much shorter avg path length. We do have heavy tail however.

Looks like its scale free double check though
Comparison with Barabasi Scale Free Network
The comparison to the Barabasi log log degree distribution shows similar to our networks log log distribution graph. This also reinforces the idea our network is scale free
